<P>I can not therefore but referr back to tho&s;e
Mi&s;erable Times, when all manner of Wicked|ne&s;s,
Profane&s;s, Contempt of God, and of his
Sabbath, broke in upon this Nation, partly by
the Connivance, and partly by the open Autho|rity
of the Crown.</P>
<P>From this wicked Practice we can not won|der,
if either on the one hand, Licentious People
the re&s;traint of the Law being taken away, took
