or that the Enemies of Revealed Re|ligion
took an Advantage from hence to mock
and make a je&s;t of Religion in General; or that
all manner of Error crept in, where &s;o gro&s;s an
Error led the way, under the &s;helter of Royal
Authority.</P>
<P>From hence began the General Debauching of
