Railery at tho&s;e, who were not able to le|vel
their Principles to the loo&s;ne&s;s of the Times.</P>
<P><HI>The Church-Yards</HI> were Throng'd every Lord's
Day with the Youths of the Country, <HI>ju&s;t like a
Market, place or a Fair;</HI> who &s;tood ready, a&s;&s;oon
<HI>as the ble&s;&s;ing was out of the Mini&s;ter's Mouth,</HI> to
