for which they were <HI>Damn'd as Schi&s;maticks,</HI>
Reproch'd as <HI>Puritans,</HI> and Preci&s;e People their
Windows often broke, and they Branded as Di&s;|loyal,
<PB N="16" REF="15">
and Di&s;affected, being they would not o|bey
the Commands of their Prince, to go to the
Devil the Shorte&s;t Way.</P>
<P>Two things had their beginning at this Period;
and tho' I do not de&s;cend to the Proof of it, for
