&s;uch thing known in this Nation, <HI>as a breaking$$
off from the Church;</HI> For the Old <HI>Puritans,</HI> al|tho'
they did Di&s;like &s;ome things, yet they
made it a point of Con&s;cience, not to break
off in Communion from the Church; and
probably never had broken off, if this Vil$
Attempt, of &s;etting up an Allowed Prophana
tion of the Lord's Day had not been made
and they pu&s;h'd at to join in it; which the
refus'd to do, from the very &s;ame Principle
