(<HI>viz.</HI>) its Source or beginning, which is
the Que&s;tion in hand; yet having fir&s;t prov'd un|denyably,
that the Source or Original of the&s;e
things was not rightly placed; and this I think
is plain, <HI>I &s;hall not &s;tick to grant them,</HI> that tho&s;e
beginnings of Mi&s;chief, <HI>tho' ri&s;en to a Deluge be|fore
the &s;aid War,</HI> yet receiv'd a Great Addition
