of the Government, which no
doubt would agree to it; which if Profecuted, as the Law does already su|ficiently
Direct and allow; would in
a few Years be totally and effectually
Di&s;couraged, and Suppre&s;s'd.</P>
<P>One Thing more might be added
here; and which, <HI>next to the In&s;truction
of the Youth,</HI> is the mo&s;t Effectual Step
that can be taken; towards the taking
away all Danger of the Peoples being
Debauched into Error; and the Omi&s;|&s;ion
of which, perhaps is at pre&s;ent the
Chief Rea&s;on why they are &s;o ea&s;ily led
<PB N="27" REF="26">
away from the Church. <HI>And this is</HI> the
Effectual Reformation of the Clergy of
the Church of <HI>England;</HI> which howe|ver
the Convocation have thought fit to
leave wholly out of their Repre&s;entation
